#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 2.3.0 Release Notes"
msgstr "NumPy 2.3.0 發行備註"

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:7
msgid ""
"The NumPy 2.3.0 release continues the work to improve free threaded Python "
"support and annotations together with the usual set of bug fixes. It is "
"unusual in the number of expired deprecations, code modernizations, and "
"style cleanups. The latter may not be visible to users, but is important for "
"code maintenance over the long term. Note that we have also upgraded from "
"manylinux2014 to manylinux_2_28."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:14
msgid ""
"Users running on a Mac having an M4 cpu might see various warnings about "
"invalid values and such. The warnings are a known problem with Accelerate. "
"They are annoying, but otherwise harmless. Apple promises to fix them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:18
msgid ""
"This release supports Python versions 3.11-3.13, Python 3.14 will be "
"supported when it is released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:23
msgid "Highlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:25
msgid "Interactive examples in the NumPy documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:26
msgid "Building NumPy with OpenMP Parallelization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:27
msgid "Preliminary support for Windows on ARM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:28
msgid "Improved support for free threaded Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:29
msgid "Improved annotations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:33
msgid "New functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:36
msgid "New function ``numpy.strings.slice``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:37
msgid ""
"The new function ``numpy.strings.slice`` was added, which implements fast "
"native slicing of string arrays. It supports the full slicing API including "
"negative slice offsets and steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:41
msgid "(`gh-27789 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27789>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:45
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:47
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.typing.mypy_plugin`` has been deprecated in favor of platform-"
"agnostic static type inference. Please remove ``numpy.typing.mypy_plugin`` "
"from the ``plugins`` section of your mypy configuration. If this change "
"results in new errors being reported, kindly open an issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:52
msgid "(`gh-28129 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28129>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:54
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.typing.NBitBase`` type has been deprecated and will be removed "
"in a future version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:57
msgid ""
"This type was previously intended to be used as a generic upper bound for "
"type-parameters, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:60
msgid ""
"import numpy as np\n"
"import numpy.typing as npt\n"
"\n"
"def f[NT: npt.NBitBase](x: np.complexfloating[NT]) -> np.floating[NT]: ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:67
msgid ""
"But in NumPy 2.2.0, ``float64`` and ``complex128`` were changed to concrete "
"subtypes, causing static type-checkers to reject ``x: np.float64 = f(np."
"complex128(42j))``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:71
msgid "So instead, the better approach is to use ``typing.overload``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:73
msgid ""
"import numpy as np\n"
"from typing import overload\n"
"\n"
"@overload\n"
"def f(x: np.complex64) -> np.float32: ...\n"
"@overload\n"
"def f(x: np.complex128) -> np.float64: ...\n"
"@overload\n"
"def f(x: np.clongdouble) -> np.longdouble: ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:85
msgid "(`gh-28884 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28884>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:89
msgid "Expired deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:91
msgid ""
"Remove deprecated macros like ``NPY_OWNDATA`` from Cython interfaces in "
"favor of ``NPY_ARRAY_OWNDATA`` (deprecated since 1.7)"
msgstr ""

