#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:96
msgid ""
"Remove ``numpy/npy_1_7_deprecated_api.h`` and C macros like ``NPY_OWNDATA`` "
"in favor of ``NPY_ARRAY_OWNDATA`` (deprecated since 1.7)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:101
msgid ""
"Remove alias ``generate_divbyzero_error`` to "
"``npy_set_floatstatus_divbyzero`` and ``generate_overflow_error`` to "
"``npy_set_floatstatus_overflow`` (deprecated since 1.10)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:107
msgid "Remove ``np.tostring`` (deprecated since 1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:111
msgid "Raise on ``np.conjugate`` of non-numeric types (deprecated since 1.13)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:115
msgid ""
"Raise when using ``np.bincount(...minlength=None)``, use 0 instead "
"(deprecated since 1.14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:120
msgid ""
"Passing ``shape=None`` to functions with a non-optional shape argument "
"errors, use ``()`` instead (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:125
msgid ""
"Inexact matches for ``mode`` and ``searchside`` raise (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:129
msgid "Setting ``__array_finalize__ = None`` errors (deprecated since 1.23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:133
msgid ""
"``np.fromfile`` and ``np.fromstring`` error on bad data, previously they "
"would guess (deprecated since 1.18)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:138
msgid ""
"``datetime64`` and ``timedelta64`` construction with a tuple no longer "
"accepts an ``event`` value, either use a two-tuple of (unit, num) or a 4-"
"tuple of (unit, num, den, 1) (deprecated since 1.14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:144
msgid ""
"When constructing a ``dtype`` from a class with a ``dtype`` attribute, that "
"attribute must be a dtype-instance rather than a thing that can be parsed as "
"a dtype instance (deprecated in 1.19). At some point the whole construct of "
"using a dtype attribute will be deprecated (see #25306)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:151
msgid "Passing booleans as partition index errors (deprecated since 1.23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:155
msgid ""
"Out-of-bounds indexes error even on empty arrays (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:159
msgid ""
"``np.tostring`` has been removed, use ``tobytes`` instead (deprecated since "
"1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:163
msgid ""
"Disallow make a non-writeable array writeable for arrays with a base that do "
"not own their data (deprecated since 1.17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:168
msgid ""
"``concatenate()`` with ``axis=None`` uses ``same-kind`` casting by default, "
"not ``unsafe`` (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:173
msgid "Unpickling a scalar with object dtype errors (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:177
msgid ""
"The binary mode of ``fromstring`` now errors, use ``frombuffer`` instead "
"(deprecated since 1.14)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:182
msgid ""
"Converting ``np.inexact`` or ``np.floating`` to a dtype errors (deprecated "
"since 1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:187
msgid ""
"Converting ``np.complex``, ``np.integer``, ``np.signedinteger``, ``np."
"unsignedinteger``, ``np.generic`` to a dtype errors (deprecated since 1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:193
msgid ""
"The Python built-in ``round`` errors for complex scalars. Use ``np.round`` "
"or ``scalar.round`` instead (deprecated since 1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:198
msgid ""
"'np.bool' scalars can no longer be interpreted as an index (deprecated since "
"1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:202
msgid ""
"Parsing an integer via a float string is no longer supported. (deprecated "
"since 1.23) To avoid this error you can * make sure the original data is "
"stored as integers. * use the ``converters=float`` keyword argument. * Use "
"``np.loadtxt(...).astype(np.int64)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:210
msgid ""
"The use of a length 1 tuple for the ufunc ``signature`` errors. Use "
"``dtype`` or  fill the tuple with ``None`` (deprecated since 1.19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:215
msgid ""
"Special handling of matrix is in np.outer is removed. Convert to a ndarray "
"via ``matrix.A`` (deprecated since 1.20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:220
msgid "Removed the ``np.compat`` package source code (removed in 2.0)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:222
msgid "(`gh-28961 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28961>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:226
msgid "C API changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:228
msgid ""
"``NpyIter_GetTransferFlags`` is now available to check if the iterator needs "
"the Python API or if casts may cause floating point errors (FPE).  FPEs can "
"for example be set when casting ``float64(1e300)`` to ``float32`` (overflow "
"to infinity) or a NaN to an integer (invalid value)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:233 ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:490
msgid "(`gh-27883 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27883>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:235
msgid "``NpyIter`` now has no limit on the number of operands it supports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:237 ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:348
msgid "(`gh-28080 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28080>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:240
msgid ""
"New ``NpyIter_GetTransferFlags`` and ``NpyIter_IterationNeedsAPI`` change"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:241
msgid ""
"NumPy now has the new ``NpyIter_GetTransferFlags`` function as a more "
"precise way checking of iterator/buffering needs.  I.e. whether the Python "
"API/GIL is required or floating point errors may occur. This function is "
"also faster if you already know your needs without buffering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:246
msgid ""
"The ``NpyIter_IterationNeedsAPI`` function now performs all the checks that "
"were previously performed at setup time.  While it was never necessary to "
"call it multiple times, doing so will now have a larger cost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:250
msgid "(`gh-27998 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27998>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:254
msgid "New Features"
msgstr "新功能"

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:256
msgid ""
"The type parameter of ``np.dtype`` now defaults to ``typing.Any``. This way, "
"static type-checkers will infer ``dtype: np.dtype`` as ``dtype: np."
"dtype[Any]``, without reporting an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:260
msgid "(`gh-28669 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28669>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:262
msgid "Static type-checkers now interpret:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:264
msgid "``_: np.ndarray`` as ``_: npt.NDArray[typing.Any]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:265
msgid "``_: np.flatiter`` as ``_: np.flatiter[np.ndarray]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:267
msgid "This is because their type parameters now have default values."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:269
msgid "(`gh-28940 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28940>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:272
msgid "NumPy now registers its pkg-config paths with the pkgconf_ PyPI package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:273
msgid ""
"The pkgconf_ PyPI package provides an interface for projects like NumPy to "
"register their own paths to be added to the pkg-config search path. This "
"means that when using pkgconf_ from PyPI, NumPy will be discoverable without "
"needing for any custom environment configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:278
msgid "Attention"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:280
msgid ""
"This only applies when using the pkgconf_ package from PyPI_, or put another "
"way, this only applies when installing pkgconf_ via a Python package manager."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:284
msgid ""
"If you are using ``pkg-config`` or ``pkgconf`` provided by your system, or "
"any other source that does not use the pkgconf-pypi_ project, the NumPy pkg-"
"config directory will not be automatically added to the search path. In "
"these situations, you might want to use ``numpy-config``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:294
msgid "(`gh-28214 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28214>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:297
msgid "Allow ``out=...`` in ufuncs to ensure array result"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:298
msgid ""
"NumPy has the sometimes difficult behavior that it currently usually returns "
"scalars rather than 0-D arrays (even if the inputs were 0-D arrays). This is "
"especially problematic for non-numerical dtypes (e.g. ``object``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:302
msgid ""
"For ufuncs (i.e. most simple math functions) it is now possible to use "
"``out=...`` (literally \\`...\\`, e.g. ``out=Ellipsis``) which is identical "
"in behavior to ``out`` not being passed, but will ensure a non-scalar "
"return. This spelling is borrowed from ``arr1d[0, ...]`` where the ``...`` "
"also ensures a non-scalar return."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:308
msgid ""
"Other functions with an ``out=`` kwarg should gain support eventually. "
"Downstream libraries that interoperate via ``__array_ufunc__`` or "
"``__array_function__`` may need to adapt to support this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:312
msgid "(`gh-28576 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28576>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:315
msgid "Building NumPy with OpenMP Parallelization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:316
msgid ""
"NumPy now supports OpenMP parallel processing capabilities when built with "
"the ``-Denable_openmp=true`` Meson build flag. This feature is disabled by "
"default. When enabled, ``np.sort`` and ``np.argsort`` functions can utilize "
"OpenMP for parallel thread execution, improving performance for these "
"operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:321 ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:404
msgid "(`gh-28619 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28619>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:324
msgid "Interactive examples in the NumPy documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:325
msgid ""
"The NumPy documentation includes a number of examples that can now be run "
"interactively in your browser using WebAssembly and Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:329
msgid ""
"Please note that the examples are currently experimental in nature and may "
"not work as expected for all methods in the public API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:333
msgid "(`gh-26745 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/26745>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:337
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:339
msgid ""
"Scalar comparisons between non-comparable dtypes such as ``np.array(1) == np."
"array('s')`` now return a NumPy bool instead of a Python bool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:343
msgid "(`gh-27288 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27288>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:345
msgid ""
"``np.nditer`` now has no limit on the number of supported operands (C-"
"integer)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:350
msgid ""
"No-copy pickling is now supported for any array that can be transposed to a "
"C-contiguous array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:353
msgid "(`gh-28105 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28105>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:355
msgid ""
"The ``__repr__`` for user-defined dtypes now prefers the ``__name__`` of the "
"custom dtype over a more generic name constructed from its ``kind`` and "
"``itemsize``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:359
msgid "(`gh-28250 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28250>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:361
msgid "``np.dot`` now reports floating point exceptions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:363
msgid "(`gh-28442 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28442>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:365
msgid ""
"``np.dtypes.StringDType`` is now a `generic type <https://typing.python.org/"
"en/latest/spec/generics.html>`_ which accepts a type argument for "
"``na_object`` that defaults to ``typing.Never``. For example, "
"``StringDType(na_object=None)`` returns a ``StringDType[None]``, and "
"``StringDType()`` returns a ``StringDType[typing.Never]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:371
msgid "(`gh-28856 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28856>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:374
msgid "Added warnings to ``np.isclose``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:375
msgid ""
"Added warning messages if at least one of atol or rtol are either ``np.nan`` "
"or ``np.inf`` within ``np.isclose``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:378
msgid "Warnings follow the user's ``np.seterr`` settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:380
msgid "(`gh-28205 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28205>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:384
msgid "Performance improvements and changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:387
msgid "Performance improvements to ``np.unique``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:388
msgid ""
"``np.unique`` now tries to use a hash table to find unique values instead of "
"sorting values before finding unique values. This is limited to certain "
"dtypes for now, and the function is now faster for those dtypes. The "
"function now also exposes a ``sorted`` parameter to allow returning unique "
"values as they were found, instead of sorting them afterwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:394 ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:470
msgid "(`gh-26018 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/26018>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:397
msgid "Performance improvements to ``np.sort`` and ``np.argsort``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:398
msgid ""
"``np.sort`` and ``np.argsort`` functions now can leverage OpenMP for "
"parallel thread execution, resulting in up to 3.5x speedups on x86 "
"architectures with AVX2 or AVX-512 instructions. This opt-in feature "
"requires NumPy to be built with the -Denable_openmp Meson flag. Users can "
"control the number of threads used by setting the OMP_NUM_THREADS "
"environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:407
msgid "Performance improvements for ``np.float16`` casts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:408
msgid ""
"Earlier, floating point casts to and from ``np.float16`` types were emulated "
"in software on all platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:411
msgid ""
"Now, on ARM devices that support Neon float16 intrinsics (such as recent "
"Apple Silicon), the native float16 path is used to achieve the best "
"performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:415
msgid "(`gh-28769 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28769>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:418
msgid "Performance improvements for ``np.matmul``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:419
msgid ""
"Enable using BLAS for ``matmul`` even when operands are non-contiguous by "
"copying if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:422
msgid "(`gh-23752 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/23752>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:425
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:427
msgid ""
"The vector norm ``ord=inf`` and the matrix norms ``ord={1, 2, inf, 'nuc'}`` "
"now always returns zero for empty arrays. Empty arrays have at least one "
"axis of size zero. This affects ``np.linalg.norm``, ``np.linalg."
"vector_norm``, and ``np.linalg.matrix_norm``. Previously, NumPy would raises "
"errors or return zero depending on the shape of the array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:433
msgid "(`gh-28343 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28343>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:435
msgid ""
"A spelling error in the error message returned when converting a string to a "
"float with the method ``np.format_float_positional`` has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:438
msgid "(`gh-28569 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28569>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:440
msgid ""
"NumPy's ``__array_api_version__`` was upgraded from ``2023.12`` to "
"``2024.12``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:442
msgid ""
"``numpy.count_nonzero`` for ``axis=None`` (default) now returns a NumPy "
"scalar instead of a Python integer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:445
msgid ""
"The parameter ``axis`` in ``numpy.take_along_axis`` function has now a "
"default value of ``-1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:448
msgid "(`gh-28615 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28615>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:450
msgid ""
"Printing of ``np.float16`` and ``np.float32`` scalars and arrays have been "
"improved by adjusting the transition to scientific notation based on the "
"floating point precision. A new legacy ``np.printoptions`` mode ``'2.2'`` "
"has been added for backwards compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:454
msgid "(`gh-28703 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28703>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:456
msgid ""
"Multiplication between a string and integer now raises OverflowError instead "
"of MemoryError if the result of the multiplication would create a string "
"that is too large to be represented. This follows Python's behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:460
msgid "(`gh-29060 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29060>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:463
msgid "``unique_values`` may return unsorted data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:464
msgid ""
"The relatively new function (added in NumPy 2.0) ``unique_values`` may now "
"return unsorted results.  Just as ``unique_counts`` and ``unique_all`` these "
"never guaranteed a sorted result, however, the result was sorted until now.  "
"In cases where these do return a sorted result, this may change in future "
"releases to improve performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:473
msgid "Changes to the main iterator and potential numerical changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:474
msgid ""
"The main iterator, used in math functions and via ``np.nditer`` from Python "
"and ``NpyIter`` in C, now behaves differently for some buffered iterations.  "
"This means that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:478
msgid ""
"The buffer size used will often be smaller than the maximum buffer sized "
"allowed by the ``buffersize`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:481
msgid ""
"The \"growinner\" flag is now honored with buffered reductions when no "
"operand requires buffering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:484
msgid ""
"For ``np.sum()`` such changes in buffersize may slightly change numerical "
"results of floating point operations.  Users who use \"growinner\" for "
"custom reductions could notice changes in precision (for example, in NumPy "
"we removed it from ``einsum`` to avoid most precision changes and improve "
"precision for some 64bit floating point inputs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:493
msgid "The minimum supported GCC version is now 9.3.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:494
msgid ""
"The minimum supported version was updated from 8.4.0 to 9.3.0, primarily in "
"order to reduce the chance of platform-specific bugs in old GCC versions "
"from causing issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:498
msgid "(`gh-28102 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28102>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:501
msgid "Changes to automatic bin selection in numpy.histogram"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:502
msgid ""
"The automatic bin selection algorithm in ``numpy.histogram`` has been "
"modified to avoid out-of-memory errors for samples with low variation.  For "
"full control over the selected bins the user can use set the ``bin`` or "
"``range`` parameters of ``numpy.histogram``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:507
msgid "(`gh-28426 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28426>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:510
msgid "Build manylinux_2_28 wheels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:511
msgid ""
"Wheels for linux systems will use the ``manylinux_2_28`` tag (instead of the "
"``manylinux2014`` tag), which means dropping support for redhat7/centos7, "
"amazonlinux2, debian9, ubuntu18.04, and other pre-glibc2.28 operating system "
"versions, as per the `PEP 600 support table`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:518
msgid "(`gh-28436 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28436>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:521
msgid "Remove use of -Wl,-ld_classic on macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.3.0-notes.rst:522
msgid ""
"Remove use of -Wl,-ld_classic on macOS. This hack is no longer needed by "
"Spack, and results in libraries that cannot link to other libraries built "
"with ld (new)."
msgstr ""

